---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
---
<Base title="Affiliate disclosure" description="How MoodSupplement earns money through affiliate links, in plain language.">
  <Breadcrumb crumbs={[
    { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
    { label: 'Affiliate disclosure' },
  ]} />
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-6 pb-16">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Trust</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-moss-deep">Affiliate disclosure</h1>
    <div class="prose-mr mt-6">
      <p>MoodSupplement is a reader-supported site. Some of the links on our supplement pages are affiliate links — mostly to Amazon, and in some cases direct to a brand's own store (for example Sports Research, through the Rakuten Advertising network). If you click one of these links and make a purchase, we may earn a commission — at no additional cost to you.</p>
      <p><strong>As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases.</strong></p>
      <p>Commission rates differ between programs. They do not decide our picks: every recommendation has to clear the published quality criterion on that product's page, and we say plainly when a product fails it.</p>
      <p>We disclose this clearly because it's the right thing to do and because the FTC requires it. Affiliate links are labelled on the page and marked with <code>rel="sponsored"</code> in the underlying code.</p>
      <h2>Our promise</h2>
      <p>Earning a commission never changes what we write. Our evidence ratings, the cautions we include, and the supplements we choose to feature are decided independently of any commercial relationship. If a supplement carries a serious interaction risk, we say so prominently regardless of whether it might cost us a sale.</p>

    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
